Here's how to implement all three requirements:

**1 & 2. Guard navigation with a confirmation dialog in `AppShell.xaml.cs`:**

```csharp
protected override async void OnNavigating(ShellNavigatingEventArgs args)
{
    base.OnNavigating(args);

    if (args.Source == ShellNavigationSource.Pop
        && Shell.Current.CurrentPage is EditProductPage page
        && page.HasUnsavedChanges)
    {
        var deferral = args.GetDeferral();

        bool discard = await Shell.Current.CurrentPage
            .DisplayAlert("Unsaved Changes",
                          "Discard changes?",
                          "Discard", "Stay");

        if (!discard)
            args.Cancel();

        deferral.Complete();
    }
}
```

Key points:
- **`GetDeferral()`** is required because `DisplayAlert` is async â€” without it the navigation completes before the dialog returns.
- **`args.Cancel()`** stops the navigation if the user taps "Stay".
- Check `ShellNavigationSource.Pop` so the guard only fires on back navigation, not forward pushes.

**3. Custom "Cancel" back button on `EditProductPage.xaml`:**

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             x:Class="MyApp.Views.EditProductPage"
             Title="Edit Product">

    <Shell.BackButtonBehavior>
        <BackButtonBehavior TextOverride="Cancel"
                           Command="{Binding CancelCommand}" />
    </Shell.BackButtonBehavior>

    <!-- page content -->
</ContentPage>
```

If you use `Command` here, the command handler replaces the default back action, so navigate manually:

```csharp
// In your ViewModel
[RelayCommand]
async Task Cancel()
{
    // The OnNavigating guard above will still fire,
    // showing the confirmation dialog automatically.
    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
}
```

> **Tip:** If you don't need custom command logic and just want the text label change, omit `Command` â€” the default back behavior (which triggers `OnNavigating`) is preserved, and you only set `TextOverride="Cancel"`.
